---
source: src/cli.rs
expression: help
---
Kuma test harness

Usage: harness [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  hook                Run a harness hook for a skill
  init                Initialize a new test run
  bootstrap           Install or refresh the repo-aware harness wrapper
  cluster             Manage disposable local k3d clusters
  preflight           Run preflight checks and prepare suite manifests
  capture             Capture cluster pod state for a run
  record              Record a tracked command
  restart-namespace   Restart deployments in specified namespaces
  apply               Apply manifests to the cluster
  validate            Validate manifests against the cluster
  runner-state        Manage runner workflow state
  closeout            Close out a run
  report              Report validation and group finalization
  diff                View diffs between payloads
  envoy               Envoy admin operations
  gateway             Check or install Gateway API CRDs
  kumactl             Find or build kumactl
  session-start       Handle session start hook
  session-stop        Handle session stop cleanup
  pre-compact         Save compact handoff before compaction
  authoring-begin     Begin a suite:new workspace session
  authoring-save      Save a suite:new payload
  authoring-show      Show saved suite:new payloads
  authoring-reset     Reset suite:new workspace
  authoring-validate  Validate authored manifests against local CRDs
  approval-begin      Begin suite:new approval flow
  api                 Call the Kuma control plane REST API directly
  token               Generate a dataplane token from the control plane (universal mode)
  service             Manage universal mode test service containers
  status              Show cluster state as structured JSON
  logs                Show container logs
  cluster-check       Check if cluster containers are still running
  task                Read or wait for background task output
  capabilities        Report harness capabilities for skill planning
  observe             Observe and classify Claude Code session logs
  help                Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --delay <DELAY>  Seconds to wait before executing the command. Accepts fractional values (e.g. 0.5). Use instead of `sleep N && harness ...` [default: 0]
  -h, --help           Print help
  -V, --version        Print version
